data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
This product feature tour is designed to expose you to the most commonly used features in CallButler. If you haven't yet completed the Quick Start Wizard, this tour can also be used as a step-by-step guide to setting up CallButler for your business.
Please click the Next > button to begin your tour.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value:
Extensions are an important and powerful part of the CallButler telephone system. With an extension you can take voicemails or transfer a caller to a real person on a mobile or land based telephone anywhere in the world. Callers may either enter extensions directly or search for them using their telephone keypad.
In most cases you will want to create an extension for every employee in your company who may need to be contacted by an outside caller. However, extensions don't need to be tied to individual people. I some cases you may want to create an extension for general voicemail messages and other uses.
To add extensions, press the Next > button, then click the Add a new extension button at the bottom of the screen.

data.name: label4.Text
data.value:
The Call Flow is a simplified visual representation of the path or 'flow' your callers will take when they connect to your answering system. The call flow is read from left to right and starts with welcome greeting and ends with the selection of an option or department.
To begin, you should record your welcome greeting. Your welcome greeting can either be spoken by a computer voice or recorded with your own voice. To do this, click on the Change button below the Welcome Greeting box.
After you record your welcome greeting you should define your departments or menu options. Departments can relay certain information to your callers (like hours, directions, etc.) or transfer callers to an extension.
Next you should record your main menu greeting to explain the available options to your callers. This can be done the same way you recorded your welcome greeting.

data.name: label5.Text
data.value:
CallButler leverages the power of Voice Over IP (VoIP) to enable your phone system to run without any telephone lines. All you need is a broadband Internet connection and VoIP service. With VoIP service, you can get a local telephone number or even an 800 number so callers anywhere in the world can connect with your business.
CallButler is designed to work with any SIP compatible VoIP service, but if you don't have an existing VoIP provider we recommend using CallButler VoIP service. CallButler VoIP service will be the quickest and easiest to setup.
Would you like find out more about CallButler VoIP service?

data.name: label6.Text
data.value:
In most cases CallButler should now be ready to begin taking your phone calls. Although before you continue we recommend completing some optional last minute steps.
If you are ready to continue, please press the Finish button.
